						<summary>

						<p>Slab in the <hi rend="italic">doḍḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1045 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged record probably refers to a grant and mentions a <hi rend="italic">mahāsāmanta</hi> (name lost), Nanni-Chaḷuki and Bīvayya.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 96[7] Vaḍḍavāra. The available information is insufficient for verification. However, the Śaka year corresponds to 1045 A.D. The cyclic year was Pārthiva.</p>						

						</summary>
